President Donald J. Trump will meet with Prime Minister Narendra Modi of India at the White House on June 26, 2017. The purpose of the meeting is to discuss ways to strengthen the relationship between the United States and India, focusing on fighting terrorism, promoting economic growth and reforms, and expanding security cooperation in the Indo-Pacific region. The leaders will work towards outlining a common vision for the partnership between the two countries that benefits their combined population of 1.6 billion citizens.